
Learn to **think in growth rates**, quickly **analyze loops**, and **optimize naive solutions**. By the end, you should confidently say the **TC (and why)** for most beginner problems.
---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ What Time Complexity Really Means

### Core Idea

Time Complexity is **not the time taken**, but the **rate at which operations grow** with input size `n`.

* Independent of machine
* Focuses on scalability
* Measured in terms of primitive operations

ğŸ“Œ Interview phrase to remember:

> â€œWe analyze how the algorithm scales as input increases.â€

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Big-O, Theta, Omega (Clean Mental Model)

### Big-O â†’ Upper Bound (Worst Case)

* Maximum work algorithm can do
* Used most in interviews

### Theta â†’ Tight/Average Bound

* Typical behavior

### Omega â†’ Lower Bound (Best Case)

* Minimum possible work

âš ï¸ In practice: **use Big-O unless asked otherwise**.

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Rules You MUST Apply 

### Rule 1: Ignore Constants

```python
for i in range(5*n):   # O(n)
    pass
```

### Rule 2: Ignore Lower Order Terms

```python
O(n^2 + n + 10) â†’ O(n^2)
```

### Rule 3: Sequential Blocks Add

```python
O(n) + O(n) = O(n)
```

### Rule 4: Nested Blocks Multiply

```python
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(n):
        pass
# O(n^2)
```

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Loop Analysis Techniques (Very Important)

### Technique 1: Count Rows & Columns

* Outer loop â†’ rows
* Inner loop â†’ columns

Total operations = rows Ã— columns

---

### Technique 2: Variable Loop Bounds

```python
for i in range(n):
    for j in range(i):
        pass
```

Operations:

```
1 + 2 + 3 + ... + n = n(n+1)/2
```

ğŸ‘‰ **O(nÂ²)**

---

### Technique 3: Changing Loop Direction

```python
for i in range(n, 0, -1):
    pass
```

Still **O(n)** (direction doesnâ€™t matter)

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ When Time Complexity is Logarithmic

### Key Signal

* Input size **divides** each iteration

```python
while n > 1:
    n //= 2
```

Iterations â‰ˆ logâ‚‚(n)

ğŸ‘‰ **O(log n)**

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Competitive Programming Rule 

* ~10â¸ operations â‰ˆ 1 second

| Complexity | Max n (approx) |
| ---------- | -------------- |
| O(n)       | 10â¸            |
| O(n log n) | 10â·            |
| O(nÂ²)      | 10â´            |
| O(nÂ³)      | 500            |

Use this to **reject slow solutions early**.

